Subject: [PATCH] uu_wc: add injected-I/O logical entry for an in-process brush
 builtin
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adapt the vendored uu_wc so it runs as a native in-process brush builtin
that reads/writes the shell's logical OpenFile sink/source instead of the
process's global stdin/stdout/stderr — no process-global stdio, no dup2, so it
is safe as a concurrent pipeline stage. uumain is retained as a thin descriptor
bridge over the new entry for the standalone binary / --invoke-bundled path.
Behavior (and any fast path) is kept byte-for-byte; only the I/O seam moved.
See engine/vendor/uu_wc/src for the diff against the pristine base.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

